== Non-Player Character Movement Issue

During multiplayer testing, another character not controlled by `PlayerController` is needed. However, I used the `AIMoveto` method of `AIController` to make this character move towards the player-controlled character, but it wouldn't move at all. Initially, I thought that the `AIController` required some manual settings or initialization to take effect. However, after some research, I found that if a `Character` is not player-controlled, it is by default controlled by `AIController`, but for it to work properly, another thing is needed—`NavMesh`. The map must have this for characters to move under the control of `AIController`. So, I added a `NavMeshBoundVolume` to the scene, which marks the areas in the scene where characters can stand and move, like this:

#figure(image("/public/assets/img/2022/20221025-ue5-timesync-and-npc-movement-fix-2.png"), caption: "image.png")

After adding this, the non-player-controlled character was able to move.
